Requirements:

* Output ONLY the completed HTML above — no markdown fences, no preamble, no commentary.
* Fill every placeholder: [Article Title], [Publication Name], [Publication Date], [Article URL].
* Keep total word count under 300 words across all sections.
* Use clear professional language.
* Do not reproduce large portions of the article verbatim.
* Focus on insights over repetition.
* Highlight practical implications for AI, SaaS, engineering, or startup topics.
* Remove all marketing fluff and clickbait.
* The greeting always reads "Hello," unless a different name is available in the payload.
* Send the completed HTML email using the Gmail tool to the recipient from the webhook payload.
* Default recipient if none provided: recipient@example.com

If no new article is found since the last run, output exactly:
"No new articles published since the last digest."
